      "span_text": "Double infections by the specialist parasite do not mean that only two individual parasites are present in a host, but simply allow for re-infection of an already infected hosts to avoid bias when the generalist parasite is introduced: for co-infection models, if the resident strain (in this case, the specialist) cannot produce double infections, the co-infection model is biased [CITATION_1] ."
